The paper deals with the study of rank and dimension of the kernel for Z2Z4-linear codes, which are related to binary and quaternary linear codes. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves constructions and bounds, which are common in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Scientific Computing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of linear algebra techniques and optimization methods suggests that the paper could also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
